bio: American writer, expatriated in Paris at his flourishing.

bio: English writer, who is considered one of the foremost modernist authors of the 20th century.

bio: American novelist, poet, playwright, and art collector.

bio: American novelist and poet. Wrote On the Road.

bio: American writer whose works illustrate the Jazz Age.

name: Truman Capote
bio: American novelist, screenwriter, playwright, and actor.
